      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use Case 2: Managing Multi-Venue Teams From One Dashboard",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "This one surprised me.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Shiftie handles multi-venue scheduling natively. If you run a restaurant group, a retail chain, or a franchise with locations across town, you can view and manage every site from a single dashboard. No toggling between accounts. No duplicate setups.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A farm center with three retail areas (shop, café, and activity park) can assign staff to specific venues, track who's trained where, and fill gaps across locations when someone calls in sick. The drag-and-drop interface works identically whether you're scheduling for one venue or fifteen.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "It's the kind of feature that typically lives behind enterprise paywalls. Shiftie includes it in every plan.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use Case 3: Automating Timesheets and Payroll Prep",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Manual timesheets are where errors hide. An employee forgets to clock out. A manager misreads a handwritten log. Hours get rounded the wrong way, and suddenly someone's paycheck is off by £40.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Shiftie's time clock lets employees clock in and out directly from their phones. The system generates timesheets automatically based on actual clock-in data, not what was scheduled. Managers review, approve, and export — ready for payroll.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "I've seen businesses cut their payroll prep time from two hours to fifteen minutes with this workflow alone. That's not an exaggeration. When the data flows directly from clock-in to timesheet to export, there's simply less to go wrong.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use Case 4: Handling Leave Requests Without the Email Chain",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Every manager knows the drill: an employee emails about time off. The manager forwards it to HR. HR checks the calendar. Someone forgets to update the spreadsheet. Two people end up approved for the same week off, and now you're short-staffed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Shiftie's leave management module puts all of this in one place. Employees request time off through the app. Managers see it against the team calendar and approve or decline with a click. Approved leave automatically blocks those dates from future scheduling.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "No email threads. No crossed wires. No spreadsheet tabs named \"FINAL_v3_ACTUAL.\"",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l3",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/why-choose-shiftie"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "For more on how these features fit together, our guide on ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "why to choose Shiftie",
            "marks": [
              "l3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " breaks down the full picture.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "---",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use Case 5: Keeping the Team Connected With Built-In Messaging",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Communication gaps kill shift reliability. An employee misses an update about a schedule change. A manager can't reach someone to cover a gap.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Shiftie includes team messaging directly inside the platform. Announcements, shift reminders, and one-on-one messages all live where the schedule lives. Employees don't need to check a separate app or dig through WhatsApp threads to find out their start time changed.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "It sounds simple. It is simple. And that's exactly why it works.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
            "_key": "l4",
            "_type": "link",
            "href": "https://tonyciencia.com/en/posts/shiftie-new-features"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "See Shiftie's latest features and updates",
            "marks": [
              "l4"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " to learn what else they've added recently.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
