      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h2",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Use Case 7: Onboarding New Employees Into the Scheduling System",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Hiring seasonal staff? Bringing on a batch of new team members? Onboarding them into Shiftie takes minutes.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Add their profile, set their role, define their availability, and they're immediately visible on the scheduling calendar. They get access to the app, can view their upcoming shifts, clock in, and message the team — all from day one.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "No training session needed. The interface is intuitive enough that most employees figure it out without a manual. That's a real advantage during busy hiring seasons when you can't afford to spend an hour per person on software training.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [
          {
